<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TNT17">
<l>poṅkārmēl liḷaṅkoṅkai poṉṉē pūppap</l>
<l>porukayalkaṇ ṇīrarumpap pōntu niṉṟu</l>
<l>ceṅkāla maṭappuṟavam peṭaikkup pēcuñ</l>
<l>ciṟukuraluk kuṭalurukic cintit tāṅkē</l>
<l>taṇkālun taṇkuṭantai nakarum pāṭit</l>
<l>taṇkōva lūrppāṭi yāṭak kēṭṭu</l>
<l>naṅkāynaṅ kuṭikkituvō naṉmai yeṉṉa</l>
<l>naṟaiyūrum pāṭuvāḷna vilkiṉ ṟāḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>As her soft, heaving, young breasts grow pallid</l>
<l rend="indent">and tears keep on springing forth [from] her eyes, like opposing fish,</l>
<l>Thinking [of him], her body melting at the little coo</l>
<l rend="indent">which the rosy-legged, simple dove sounds for [his] hen,</l>
<l>Singing there of Taṇkāl and the cool city of Kuṭantai,</l>
<l rend="indent">singing of cool Kōvalūr,</l>
<l>Listening as she dances, when [I] say, “Girl, is this good for our family?”</l>
<l rend="indent">she [still] practices, she who [then] sings of Naṟaiyūr, too!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
